  id: Thigh_Bone_Femur_L
  partName: Thigh Bone Femur Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left femur forms the primary skeletal support of the canine left hindlimb
    and extends between the hip and stifle joints. This powerful bone bears substantial
    body weight while providing attachment points for muscles responsible for hip
    movement, stifle control, and hindlimb propulsion.
  - The femur contributes significantly to stability, balance, and efficient locomotion
    during running, jumping, and standing activities. Its articulations with the
    pelvis, tibia, and patella enable coordinated joint motion and force transmission.
